HEADWORD: Cynanche
<hw>Cy*nan"che</hw> <pr>(s?-n?n"k?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/<?/ a dog's collar, a bad kind of sore throat. Cf.
<er>Quinsy</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any disease of the
tonsils, throat, or windpipe, attended with inflammation, swelling, and
difficulty of breathing and swallowing.</def>⟦br⟧
